						<summary>

						<p>This inscription registers the kings gift of taxes like <hi rend="italic">ponvaṟi, Veṭṭipāṭṭam, Pañjupili, Ilañjinarpēru, Tariyiṟai, Chekkiṟai, iṉavari</hi> and <hi rend="italic">siṟṟāyam</hi> etc., due from the inhabitants <hi rend="italic">Maravar, Iḍaiyar</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Valaiyar</hi> community of the same place to the temple of Śivadharmīśvaramuḍaiyanāyaṉār for undertaking some repair works in the name of the king's elder brother <hi rend="italic">(aṉṉālvi).</hi></p>						

						</summary>
